	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hey. I just wondered if I can make a iNES/UNIF mapper emulator support c64 SID chip emulation as extra sound. 
<br />
<br />But there's one reason for doing this: After that, I will (or might, if I have the time) to try to make a hardware NES project using ''Quazar SID interface'', ''HardSID'' or something like that. It is to benefit making and listening music and/or port games to C64 and back.
<br />
<br />What do you think, Should I do this addition to the family of extra famicom sound? Vote Here

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


