		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />What would we do with the SID on NES, though? Dump .sid files to carts? Wouldn't that nessecitate emulating the C64 processor as well as the sound chip? I guess the GT dissasembler would help with this? If I could run progs from Goattracker on NES, that would be cool, but midiBox sid already can do this.
<br />
<br />There are alot of good SID hardware applications out there (midiBox for instance) already. So I don't know how useful an NesSID application would be to musicians. 
<br />
<br />Also, a SID-like substitute, if real chips do get hard to find:
<br />
